Description:
Appia Wind Services LLC is a company that focuses primarily on blade maintenance and repairs in the composite wind energy field. Other services that our company provides include blade inspections, retrofits, lightning protection system installations, and new wind farm installation support. Appia was founded in 2016 and is currently involved in several wind farm projects across more than 15 states. Our company provides rapid deployment of experienced technicians to perform effectively and efficiently. With safety compliance and engineering support, Appia is able to deliver work instruction and repairing reports for our customers. 


AWS QHSE SCOPE

Appia Wind Services LLC performs inspections,  preventive maintenance, and corrective maintenance on wind turbine components.



AWS QHSE POLICY

Appia Wind Services LLC undertakes the following commitments in its activities:
- Comply with applicable legal, customer, and statutory requirements;
- Promote the continuous improvement of the QHSE Management System;
- Protect the environment, including pollution prevention actions;
- Provide safe and healthy working conditions for the prevention of work-related injuries and illnesses;
- Eliminate hazards and reduce SSO risks;
- Consult workers and encourage their participation and that of their representatives.

SALOME will investigate a novel scientific strategy for dynamic management and predictive maintenance of offshore wind turbines by taking into consideration all the physical parameters and phenomena impacting their aging in order to facilitate a fatigue-informed participation of offshore wind farms in frequency control and in electricity markets (day-ahead and reserve). 

SALOME Consortium brings together complementary know-how of six research labs in France, Wallonia, and Flanders: 
- Advanced Photonic Sensors (APS) group, University of Mons, Belgium;
- Electrical Power Engineering Unit (EPEU), University of Mons, Belgium;
- Department of applied photonics, Multitel Research Centre, Belgium;
- Electrical Energy Laboratory (EELab), Ghent University, Belgium;
- LPCA (Laboratoire de Physico-Chimie de l'Atmosphère) and LOG (Laboratoire d'Océanologie et de Géosciences) research groups, University of the Littoral Opal Coast, France.

Champs d’Énergie est une coopérative énergétique active depuis 2013 sur la commune de Fernelmont et environs. Nous développons et finançons des projets éoliens, photovoltaïques, et biomasse. 

Les finalités de la coopérative, reflétant ses valeurs, sont les suivantes :

* La participation citoyenne à la gestion des énergies d’origine renouvelable;

* Un changement structurel en matière de production et consommation d’énergie (développement des énergies renouvelables, décentralisation de la production, efficacité énergétique et réduction de la consommation);

* L’accessibilité (économique et sociale) des citoyen·ne·s aux produits et services liés aux énergies renouvelables;

* Le développement local.
